The Queen has spread awareness about the coronavirus. After the president address on Monday evening, the popular Mzansi Magic soapie that has over one million viewers added a scene to the show to make people more aware about the coronavirus outbreak that is gradually spreading throughout South Africa. ALSO READ: VIRUS HITS ARTISTS' POCKETS In the scene Jerry Maake played by Shona Ferguson can be heard asking Thato why the Corner House is empty today, and Thato quickly jumps in to says it could be because the Corona Virus. WATCH FULL CILP HERE: #TheQueenMzansiCares #FergusonFilms @mzansimagic A post shared by  SHONA FERGUSON (@ferguson_films) on Mar 16, 2020 at 9:49am PDT 